1
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:28,450
♪Like a flock of birds
pressing ever forward♪

2
00:00:28,980 --> 00:00:33,350
♪Stranded on an island
shrouded in heavy mist♪

3
00:00:34,450 --> 00:00:38,410
♪We may seem small
beneath the vast world♪

4
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:43,680
♪But not once have we felt despair♪

5
00:00:43,970 --> 00:00:46,770
♪We've crossed waves
a thousand layers deep♪

6
00:00:46,770 --> 00:00:49,530
♪Stepped on reefs hidden in the dark♪

7
00:00:49,530 --> 00:00:54,730
♪Facing sharper winds head-on♪

8
00:00:54,730 --> 00:00:57,660
♪Our wounds now stitched
into battle robes♪

9
00:00:57,660 --> 00:01:00,370
♪The long night
is branded by starlight♪

10
00:01:00,370 --> 00:01:05,440
♪We embrace this deep blue together♪

11
00:01:05,590 --> 00:01:10,620
♪At the edge of the vast unknown,
I remain unchanged♪

12
00:01:11,070 --> 00:01:16,540
♪Holding fast with lonely courage,
roaring without fear♪

13
00:01:16,670 --> 00:01:21,850
♪Determined to be
both my friend and my rival♪

14
00:01:22,140 --> 00:01:27,030
♪No one dares to blindly
urge me to turn back♪

15
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:32,090
♪I choose what I believe is worth it♪

16
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:38,340
=Rose and Gun=

17
00:01:38,940 --> 00:01:40,980
=Episode 15=

18
00:02:00,490 --> 00:02:02,490
Are you okay? Let me see.

19
00:02:08,090 --> 00:02:08,880
Wu Si.

20
00:02:11,410 --> 00:02:13,440
Am I dreaming?

21
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:16,250
Why are you here?

22
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:19,130
We came to An
for a military competition

23
00:02:19,850 --> 00:02:21,480
and just got a notice from the Embassy

24
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:23,880
that two Chinese citizens
had gone missing nearby,

25
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:24,880
so we rushed here.

26
00:02:27,690 --> 00:02:28,690
Are you hurt?

27
00:02:39,382 --> 00:02:41,693
Did you not eat for the past few days
in the jungle?

28
00:02:42,130 --> 00:02:42,920
Are you hungry?

29
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:55,970
Do you know?

30
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,320
When I confirmed

31
00:02:58,690 --> 00:03:00,480
the two missing Chinese citizens

32
00:03:00,530 --> 00:03:01,920
were you and Yangyang,

33
00:03:02,090 --> 00:03:03,570
I was worried sick, you know?

34
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:08,980
♪Using up all my fortune♪

35
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:13,170
♪Just to trade a lifetime with you♪

36
00:03:13,410 --> 00:03:16,510
♪Thank you for awakening♪

37
00:03:16,510 --> 00:03:20,620
♪The courage once hidden in my fear♪

38
00:03:20,850 --> 00:03:23,790
♪Turning every chance into certainty♪

39
00:03:24,340 --> 00:03:27,680
♪Turning every tie into companionship♪

40
00:03:28,050 --> 00:03:34,530
♪Blooming into brilliance
for all the years to come♪

41
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:46,920
Doc, is there something wrong?

42
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:49,200
No, there's no problem with her health.

43
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:51,570
She just needs two days of rest
and to avoid moving.

44
00:03:52,290 --> 00:03:53,130
And that's all.

45
00:03:53,370 --> 00:03:53,920
Thanks.

46
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:54,690
You're welcome.

47
00:03:55,370 --> 00:03:56,090
Thank you.

48
00:04:02,010 --> 00:04:02,810
Please.

49
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,440
I see it.

50
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:12,760
Don't twist it.

51
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:16,760
Xin, please sit.

52
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:18,400
Well,

53
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:19,880
how are you?

54
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:21,200
Are you okay?

55
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:24,690
I'm good. Just a bit dehydrated.

56
00:04:24,690 --> 00:04:25,730
I'll eat something

57
00:04:25,730 --> 00:04:26,930
and rest when I get back.

58
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,320
Where's Captain Wu?

59
00:04:32,690 --> 00:04:34,130
Captain Wu

60
00:04:34,730 --> 00:04:36,400
has been exhausted
from the competition.

61
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,880
We let him nap over there.

62
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:41,730
What are you holding?

63
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:43,960
His hearing aid.

64
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:45,250
Hearing aid?

65
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:47,610
What happened?

66
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:49,170
Oh, you didn't know.

67
00:04:50,493 --> 00:04:52,026
A few days ago, during the competition,

68
00:04:52,226 --> 00:04:54,130
Captain Wu went too deep underwater
too fast,

69
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,826
and it caused temporary hearing damage.

70
00:04:58,010 --> 00:04:59,010
Is it serious?

71
00:05:00,610 --> 00:05:01,640
Pretty serious.

72
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:03,010
He couldn't hear us.

73
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:05,250
But he refused to wear it.

74
00:06:09,671 --> 00:06:11,804
He's quite good-looking
even when he's sleeping.

75
00:06:18,690 --> 00:06:20,440
Ever since we returned from Mazhan Town,

76
00:06:21,170 --> 00:06:22,640
I've been avoiding you.

77
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:26,400
You probably found that weird, right?

78
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:32,130
I bet you never figured it out.

79
00:06:39,690 --> 00:06:42,730
It wasn't about the Dayan Reef.

80
00:06:44,370 --> 00:06:47,130
I wasn't mad at you
because you kept it from me.

81
00:06:54,050 --> 00:06:54,640
It's because

82
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:56,610
for the first time in my life,
you made me a joke,

83
00:06:56,610 --> 00:06:57,490
you know?

84
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:04,930
Why do you have to be a soldier?

85
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:08,440
My parents

86
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:09,880
and all my friends know

87
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:11,130
I've always said,

88
00:07:11,130 --> 00:07:12,930
"I, Tang Xin,

89
00:07:12,930 --> 00:07:14,930
will never date a soldier."

90
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:16,760
But look at me now.

91
00:07:19,170 --> 00:07:20,690
I fell for you.

92
00:07:25,690 --> 00:07:27,520
You have no idea

93
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:29,315
how awkward it has been these days.

94
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:31,440
If this gets out,

95
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:32,893
how am I supposed to face everyone

96
00:07:32,937 --> 00:07:33,648
in Wenzhou?

97
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:45,010
Do you know you're kind of handsome?

98
00:07:51,130 --> 00:07:53,320
I still remember

99
00:07:53,490 --> 00:07:54,960
at Yangyang's wedding,

100
00:07:56,130 --> 00:07:57,370
you were wearing

101
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:59,320
that military uniform.

102
00:08:02,730 --> 00:08:04,490
My heart skipped a beat.

103
00:08:12,730 --> 00:08:15,880
Now I know how those
who are big fans of uniforms feel.

104
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:24,640
But you're not allowed
to wear that behind my back!

105
00:08:25,610 --> 00:08:26,960
If you do wear it,

106
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:29,520
you'd better not show off your charm
like you did that day.

107
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:31,840
Or else I'll lock you up

108
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:32,760
in a safe.

109
00:08:32,850 --> 00:08:33,610
You hear me?

110
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:35,490
Oh, I forgot.

111
00:08:36,490 --> 00:08:39,130
You can't hear right now.

112
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:02,490
Anyways,

113
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:04,130
thank you

114
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:07,490
for always being there

115
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:09,640
when I needed it the most.

116
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:16,320
Just now,

117
00:09:17,130 --> 00:09:19,804
I couldn't help but kiss you
in the jungle.

118
00:09:20,850 --> 00:09:21,800
Sorry about that.

119
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:24,730
It's fine.

120
00:09:29,090 --> 00:09:31,520
Why are you awake?

121
00:09:32,293 --> 00:09:34,293
You didn't hear what I said just now,
did you?

122
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,880
They said something's wrong
with your hearing.

123
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:39,370
You need a hearing aid.

124
00:09:40,626 --> 00:09:42,090
You didn't hear anything, right?

125
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,490
It's already healed.

126
00:09:46,850 --> 00:09:47,800
But it's fine.

127
00:09:48,330 --> 00:09:49,490
I can pretend

128
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:50,880
I didn't hear a thing.

129
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:56,560
You said that.

130
00:09:57,271 --> 00:09:58,760
Anyway, you didn't hear anything

131
00:09:58,760 --> 00:09:59,760
I said just now.

132
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:00,937
I didn't say anything at all.

133
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:02,130
What did you say?

134
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:04,490
Uniforms?

135
00:10:05,130 --> 00:10:06,330
Show off charm?

136
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:08,330
- Lock me up in a safe?
- Wu Si!

137
00:10:12,560 --> 00:10:13,800
I knew it.

138
00:10:14,040 --> 00:10:15,210
Cheng Yuan and you

139
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:16,760
teamed up

140
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:18,090
to get something out of me, right?

141
00:10:18,850 --> 00:10:19,760
If so,

142
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:24,250
did what you said count?

143
00:10:40,210 --> 00:10:41,450
Let's rest here for a bit.

144
00:10:41,490 --> 00:10:43,404
- I'll massage your leg.
- Okay. I need support.

145
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:02,210
Dear.

146
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:07,450
I know you're still shaken up right now.

147
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:09,920
But there are things I need to say.

148
00:11:12,450 --> 00:11:14,850
Why so serious all of a sudden?

149
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:19,680
Look. I'm not against
you coming to An

150
00:11:20,210 --> 00:11:22,010
or your search for sunflower seeds,

151
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:23,204
citrus seeds, or whatever.

152
00:11:23,450 --> 00:11:24,210
But I disapprove of

153
00:11:24,210 --> 00:11:26,400
the way you act so impulsively.

154
00:11:27,293 --> 00:11:28,450
This is a foreign country.

155
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:30,920
A place you know nothing.

156
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:32,450
Yet you just brought Xin

157
00:11:32,450 --> 00:11:33,520
into a jungle.

158
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:34,920
Did you consider the consequences?

159
00:11:36,370 --> 00:11:38,850
How could I know something like that
would happen?

160
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:42,250
I didn't know the forest was that huge

161
00:11:42,250 --> 00:11:43,280
and hard to get through.

162
00:11:44,130 --> 00:11:44,730
Yes.

163
00:11:45,210 --> 00:11:46,970
You didn't know.

164
00:11:46,970 --> 00:11:48,210
But you didn't prepare.

165
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:51,160
Luckily, you went with Xin.

166
00:11:51,515 --> 00:11:54,337
Luckily, the receptionist you asked
for help called the police in time.

167
00:11:54,610 --> 00:11:57,760
Luckily, the Embassy gave us approval
to search the forest.

168
00:11:58,850 --> 00:11:59,970
Only with all those lucks

169
00:11:59,970 --> 00:12:01,680
can you be standing here,
safe and sound.

170
00:12:03,010 --> 00:12:03,680
Dear,

171
00:12:04,493 --> 00:12:05,800
if the tiniest misstep happens,

172
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,850
I don't even dare to think about
what might've happened.

173
00:12:07,850 --> 00:12:09,640
Why are you scaring me?

174
00:12:10,330 --> 00:12:12,680
I didn't know we'd get lost.

175
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:14,610
I'm not trying to scare you.

176
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,210
I'm really worried.

177
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:22,370
Zong Qing,

178
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:25,330
did you come here straight

179
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:28,490
after the competition without resting?

180
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,800
You went missing. How could I rest?

181
00:12:41,520 --> 00:12:42,610
I'm sorry.

182
00:12:43,010 --> 00:12:44,370
I know I was wrong.

183
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:47,920
I won't make trouble for you again.

184
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:50,330
What are you talking about?

185
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:53,250
It's not about you making trouble.

186
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:55,490
I'm afraid you'd get hurt, you get that?

187
00:12:56,850 --> 00:12:57,680
Well.

188
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:00,640
I swear it won't happen again.

189
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:04,680
Keep your word.

190
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:12,010
Lean on it. I'll massage you.

191
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:15,520
It's fine. You should rest.

192
00:13:15,850 --> 00:13:17,210
You look exhausted.

193
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:19,537
I'm heading back to the unit soon.

194
00:13:19,537 --> 00:13:20,760
I don't have much time to rest.

195
00:13:21,826 --> 00:13:22,640
Lean on the railing.

196
00:13:27,970 --> 00:13:28,640
Is it here?

197
00:13:37,970 --> 00:13:38,970
Do you remember

198
00:13:40,210 --> 00:13:41,730
what I said to you in Wenzhou?

199
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:44,370
I told you the choice was yours.

200
00:13:46,850 --> 00:13:47,850
I mean it.

201
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:52,040
If you haven't decided yet,

202
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:53,560
I can pretend

203
00:13:53,560 --> 00:13:54,560
I didn't hear

204
00:13:54,610 --> 00:13:55,680
what you said just now.

205
00:13:55,730 --> 00:13:56,850
I'll give you more time.

206
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:10,400
I grew up in a military camp

207
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,640
with my mom

208
00:14:12,715 --> 00:14:14,893
until my dad was transferred,
and we moved away.

209
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:18,800
So the army

210
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:22,210
has always made me feel safe.

211
00:14:25,970 --> 00:14:27,680
When I think back,

212
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:30,520
there was a fair share of regrets
in my childhood.

213
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:34,210
But deep down,

214
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:37,370
I never resented my dad.

215
00:14:41,760 --> 00:14:42,880
So I know

216
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:47,130
I'm just contradicting myself

217
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:52,160
when I say I'd never marry a soldier.

218
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:56,730
I know.

219
00:15:00,370 --> 00:15:01,640
I understand your concerns,

220
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,330
and I respect that.

221
00:15:07,610 --> 00:15:08,680
I won't pressure you.

222
00:15:09,048 --> 00:15:10,330
Don't pressure yourself either.

223
00:15:11,426 --> 00:15:13,093
I'll wait until you've made your mind,

224
00:15:14,915 --> 00:15:16,490
and until you know you won't regret

225
00:15:17,640 --> 00:15:18,640
choosing me.

226
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:23,560
♪You're the extraordinary one
in the ordinary world♪

227
00:15:24,010 --> 00:15:29,030
♪The most precious moment in my life♪

228
00:15:29,270 --> 00:15:32,150
♪The promise I made to you♪

229
00:15:32,150 --> 00:15:35,330
♪Still warms my heart♪

230
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:39,420
♪Prompting me to chase the next galaxy♪

231
00:15:40,730 --> 00:15:45,360
♪You're the one, the longing, the flame♪

232
00:15:46,170 --> 00:15:51,100
♪The choice I'll never regret♪

233
00:15:51,730 --> 00:15:54,200
♪Across the raging tides♪

234
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:57,340
♪All I want is to hold you tight♪

235
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:00,210
Captain Wu, you can wrap it up.

236
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:01,740
Actually, I..

237
00:16:01,740 --> 00:16:03,790
♪It's your eyes♪

238
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:04,490
Copy.

239
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:07,210
Okay. Attention, assemble.

240
00:16:07,271 --> 00:16:08,090
- Copy.
- Copy.

241
00:16:09,330 --> 00:16:10,610
Are you leaving?

242
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:13,880
The police will escort you back.

243
00:16:14,520 --> 00:16:16,160
I need to head back
to the training camp.

244
00:16:21,090 --> 00:16:23,490
Hold on. You...

245
00:16:23,850 --> 00:16:25,680
Can you not leave just yet?

246
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:27,680
Is there anything else?

247
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:36,680
Don't you have any questions for me?

248
00:16:38,250 --> 00:16:39,400
What questions?

249
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:42,970
Um...

250
00:16:44,250 --> 00:16:47,680
Is there anything you want to ask me?

251
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,370
Keep thinking.

252
00:17:02,370 --> 00:17:04,490
Tang Xin, will you be my girlfriend?

253
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:08,250
That's the question?

254
00:17:09,690 --> 00:17:12,210
You didn't have to be

255
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:14,010
so loud.

256
00:17:16,890 --> 00:17:17,730
Well,

257
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:19,970
that's my question.

258
00:17:21,970 --> 00:17:23,040
Can you answer it?

259
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:28,970
I...

260
00:17:30,170 --> 00:17:31,320
If you don't answer me,

261
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:34,210
I should get going.

262
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:36,210
I...

263
00:17:36,690 --> 00:17:37,320
I...

264
00:17:38,040 --> 00:17:39,650
I...

265
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:40,730
I...

266
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:42,690
I...

267
00:17:46,520 --> 00:17:48,560
I will

268
00:17:49,690 --> 00:17:51,210
be your girlfriend.

269
00:17:55,890 --> 00:17:57,560
Why is he walking so fast?

270
00:18:15,170 --> 00:18:16,120
Slow down.

271
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:27,010
Get on first. Let me help you up.

272
00:18:59,020 --> 00:19:02,780
(Chinese Navy)

273
00:19:06,410 --> 00:19:07,080
Get off.

274
00:19:20,340 --> 00:19:23,540
(Chinese Navy)

275
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:24,730
Eyes right.

276
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:26,760
Eyes front.

277
00:19:27,170 --> 00:19:28,120
Turn right.

278
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:29,650
Double time, move.

279
00:19:34,540 --> 00:19:35,940
(Chinese People's Liberation Army)

280
00:19:49,060 --> 00:19:51,820
(First Place)

281
00:19:51,820 --> 00:19:53,715
(International Military Training
Competition Summary 2019)

282
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:56,170
Not bad.

283
00:19:57,450 --> 00:19:58,930
Your hard-earned reward.

284
00:20:00,080 --> 00:20:01,450
But remember,

